      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Have you tried using canvas-\u003edrawBitmapRect()?  It kind of wraps up this scaling logic in a slightly friendlier way.\n\nHmm, it\u0027s not obvious to me how drawBitmapRect would be friendlier in this case. This scale is pretty straight-forward, but I don\u0027t actually want to draw all of this-\u003edimensions(). If I were to pass dirty_rect (converted to an SkRect) as src to drawBitmapRect I\u0027d need to scale it by this matrix to find the dst SkRect, or am I missing something?\n\n\u003e Speaking of scaling, have you played around with different SkPaint::setFilterQuality() levels?  Is this always used to scale downward, or upward too?\n\nIt\u0027s only used to scale downward currently. I\u0027ve tried a few filter qualities primarily when drawing incomplete interlaced images. They look fuzzy, as we\u0027ve blended the lines that have been decoded with transparent lines between them.",
